# Agentic Skills Integration
# Always check `.agent/skills.yaml` to see available specialized skills.
# If the user asks for Python tasks, testing, or documentation, READ the corresponding SKILL.md file in `.agent/skills/` BEFORE proceeding.

- Python Development: Read `.agent/skills/python-pro/SKILL.md`
- Testing/QA: Read `.agent/skills/python-testing-patterns/SKILL.md` or `.agent/skills/lint-and-validate/SKILL.md`
- Documentation: Read `.agent/skills/documentation-generation-doc-generate/SKILL.md`
- PRs: Read `.agent/skills/git-pr-workflows-pr-enhance/SKILL.md`

# CLI usage
When running `context-engineer` CLI, prefer using the `--skill` flag to inject context:
`ce <command> --skill <skill_alias>`
